            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1289369057,
            "creation_date": 1289368751,
            "body": "<p>You could use <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/Runtime.html#exec%28java.lang.String%29\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>Runtime.exec<\/code><\/a> and pass it <code>cmd /c /path/to/your/batch/script<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>As of Java 1.5, you can also use <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/ProcessBuilder.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>ProcessBuilder<\/code><\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> Process p = new ProcessBuilder(\"cmd\", \"/c\", \"/path/to/batch/file\").start();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The API docs for <code>ProcessBuilder<\/code> details a more complex setup with working directories and such.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4141655,
            "question_id": 4141645,
            "last_edit_date": 1289369057
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/58a74af747c6637c67a6298bbfa3ac4e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 217213,
